{"word":"γεμίζω","slug":"γεμίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γεμίζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γέμω'><el>γέμω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to fill full of, to load</i> or <i>freight with</i>, a cargo of a ship, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>σποδοῦ γ. λέβητας</el> <i>charging</i> the urns <i>with</i> ashes, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be laden</i> or <i>freighted</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>later in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>οἶνον γεμισθείς</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}